      "content": "It's completely understandable to feel overwhelmed by such constant chaos, but your suffering is actually a sign that you're still engaged with the world rather than numb to it. While the news can be paralyzing, the most effective way to protect your own life is to limit your exposure to it and focus on small, manageable actions that bring you peace. You don't have to fix the world or solve the climate crisis alone; simply caring for your own well-being in the present moment is the only thing you truly control.",
